		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">jpx72 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Wow thanks for the tip! The M82 rom is perfect! It's a pitty that there isn't more graphics involved, but it's ok! <br />I'm wondering now if the Famicombox menu was dumped.. can't find it...</div>
<br />
<br />I dumped it, but it won't run on any emulators.  It needs a bunch of hardware mapped in and it needs more RAM.  It has 8K of RAM at 0000-1fff and uses 0800-1fff for the menu stuff (it can actually restrict how much RAM the game sees, and usually forces it to 0000-07fff).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
